The paper deals with controlling industrial robots in unstructured/human-centric environments, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach is based on robust control theory and convex optimization, which are fundamental topics in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as reinforcement learning and deep learning, which are relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The physical interaction tasks involve visual perception and manipulation, which are related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of uncertainty and external perturbations, which are common issues in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
